-- [IN] Official source: Indiana General Assembly, iga.in.gov. Statute text verified verbatim from the official Indiana Code PDFs (Title 32 Art. 31 Ch. 1, 3, 5; Title 16 Art. 41 Ch. 27).
-- [IN] RESIDENTIAL ACT = IC 32-31 (Landlord-Tenant Relations). It expressly reaches manufactured/mobile homes: the security-deposit chapter lists "A mobile home space" as a rental unit (IC 32-31-3-8(2)(D)), and the right-of-access chapter defines "dwelling unit" to include "A manufactured home ... or mobile structure ... and the space occupied" (IC 32-31-5-3(b)(4)). Mobile-home PARK operation, tenant ejection (IC 16-41-27-30), and innkeeper-style liens (IC 16-41-27-29) live in a separate health-code chapter, IC 16-41-27 — so mobile_home is governed by BOTH acts (general residential terms under IC 32-31; park operation/ejection under IC 16-41-27). General tenancy-notice and flood-disclosure provisions in IC 32-31-1 reach commercial property too (IC 32-31-1-21 expressly applies to "commercial property"), so commercial is tagged on the residential act; there is no dedicated Indiana commercial-tenancy act.
-- [IN] OMITTED PROVISIONS (statute specifies no value — not invented):
-- [IN] - entry_notice_hours: OMITTED. IC 32-31-5-6(g) requires only that a landlord "shall give a tenant reasonable written or oral notice of the landlord's intent to enter" and "may enter ... only at reasonable times." No fixed hour count is stated.
-- [IN] - deposit_max_months: OMITTED. IC 32-31-3 (Security Deposits) contains no cap on the deposit amount; it only restricts permitted USES (IC 32-31-3-13) and the return deadline.
-- [IN] - late_fee_max_pct: OMITTED. No Indiana statute caps residential late fees. (IC 24-7-5-5 caps late charges only for rental-PURCHASE / rent-to-own goods agreements, not residential leases — not applicable.)
-- [IN] - late_fee_grace_days: OMITTED. No statutory grace period before a residential late fee may apply.
-- [IN] NO RV-SPOT ACT: Indiana has no statute specifically governing long-term recreational-vehicle space tenancy. RVs are not "manufactured homes" (IC 22-12-1-16) or "mobile structures" (IC 22-12-1-17), so RV lot rentals are not covered by IC 16-41-27; a long-term RV occupant of a residential "dwelling/sleeping unit" could fall under IC 32-31's general residential terms, but no dedicated RV act exists.
-- [IN] NO STORAGE ACT in landlord-tenant law: self-service storage is governed separately by IC 26-3-8 (Self-Service Storage Facilities), outside Title 32 landlord-tenant relations; not included as a landlord-tenant act here.
-- [IN] Citation note: deposit return is reinforced by IC 32-31-3-14 ("Not more than forty-five (45) days after the termination of occupancy, a landlord shall mail to a tenant an itemized list of damages..."). Month-to-month context: IC 32-31-1-2 makes a general consent tenancy a tenancy from month to month, and IC 32-31-1-1 governs its termination by one (1) month's written notice.
